              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The Pu-239 samples contained 51.4 mg deposited in the",
                " form of PuO-2 on four titanium disks each with an",
                " active diameter of 40 mm was used:",
                "     masses       isotope     isotopic percentage",
                "      (mg)           A             (atoms/%)",
                "       12.8         238               0.01",
                "       13.2         239              99.01",
                "       12.8         240               0.98"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The direct measurements of number of fission fragments",
                " using the scanning of the MAKROFOL sheets by means of",
                " conventional optical microscopy.",
                "The direct measurements of photoneutrons from a total",
                " neutron production reaction (g,n-tot) and",
                " photofission reaction (g,f) - sig (g,n-tot) = sig",
                " (g,n) +  nu * sig (g,f), where nu(e) is the value of",
                " the prompt neutron multiplicity (the average number",
                " of prompt neutrons per fission)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The total errors."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-1",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Systematic uncertainty in the photopeak",
                " efficiency determination - 10%."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-2",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Systematic error in the calibration for",
                " fission counting - 3%."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-3",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Systematic error in the calibration of neutron",
                " counting - 3.6%."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-4",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Systematic error from sample atom content -",
                " 2.0%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " The error sources  were:",
                " Gamma flux - 10% of the systematic uncertainty in the",
                " photopeak efficiency determination plus 1.5 to 3%  of",
                " statistical error; photofission events - 3% of the",
                " systematic error in the calibration for fission",
                " counting plus 2 to 5% of the statistical uncertainty;",
                " photoneutron events - 3.6% of the systematic error in",
                " the calibration for neutron counting plus 6 to 10% of",
                " the statistical uncertainty; sample atom content - 2%",
                " of the  systematic error. The experimental errors in",
                " nu(e) and in the relative intensity of the  gamma-ray",
                " lines were not included in any error analysis. These",
                " values resulted in overall uncertainties of about 15%",
                " for the final photofission cross sections and about",
                " 20%  for the final total neutron cross sections. The",
                " overall uncertainties for the final photoneutron",
                " cross sections ranged from 20 to 60%.",
                "The photofission and photoneutron cross sections of",
                " Pu-239 have been measured by using monochromatic and",
                " discrete photons produced by thermal neutron capture",
                " gamma-rays in several targets placed at the core of",
                " the IAA-R1 reactor in the energy interval from 5.43",
                " to 9.72 MeV. From the photofission cross sections",
                " obtained and according to the liquid drop model, the",
                " height of the simple fission barrier was determined -",
                " f.b.  = 5.7 (0.2) MeV. The relative fissionability to",
                " U-238 was also determined and shown to be energy",
                " independent - f.r. = 3.32(0.41). The total",
                " photoabsorption cross sections were calculated as",
                " well as the photofission branching ratio or fission",
                " probability pf = 0.70 (0.06)."
              ]
            }
          ],
